WEBVTT

00:50.049 --> 00:52.469
ALL FIGURES, INCIDENTS, LOCATIONS,
ORGANIZATIONS, AND OTHERS ARE FICTITIOUS

00:52.552 --> 00:54.971
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS WERE FILMED
SAFELY IN ACCORDANCE WITH GUIDELINES

00:56.723 --> 01:01.728
EPISODE 2

01:02.979 --> 01:05.607
He suddenly started
talking nonsense like a madman.

01:05.690 --> 01:07.484
He tumbled down and bumped his head.

01:07.567 --> 01:09.694
Then, he sprawled on the floor
and blacked out--

01:09.778 --> 01:11.613
Oh, I-rang. Are you okay?

01:11.696 --> 01:13.073
Do you recognize me? Who am I?

01:13.156 --> 01:14.240
Yes, what is it?

01:15.158 --> 01:16.159
Bong-su.

01:16.242 --> 01:18.244
I'm okay, so tell them to drop us off.

01:18.328 --> 01:21.414
No, you're not okay.
You asked for an ambulance earlier.

01:21.915 --> 01:23.958
That was because I felt
too ashamed to stay there.

01:32.425 --> 01:33.635
Goodbye.

01:34.761 --> 01:36.471
I-rang, wait for me.

01:36.554 --> 01:38.264
I really don't get it, though.

01:38.348 --> 01:40.016
You're all good after tumbling that hard?

01:40.099 --> 01:42.352
- Then, was it all an act?
- An act?

01:42.435 --> 01:45.605
You suddenly swore in dialect,
pointed your finger at the defendant,

01:45.688 --> 01:47.023
and even tried to attack him.

01:47.106 --> 01:48.108
I did that?

01:48.691 --> 01:50.318
Yes, you did.

01:50.401 --> 01:52.320
You should be nominated for an Oscar.

01:52.403 --> 01:55.073
It wasn't an act! I blacked out for real.

01:56.199 --> 01:58.618
Wait. Where are you going in that state?

01:58.701 --> 01:59.869
- My office.
- What?

01:59.953 --> 02:02.080
I can't go on like this.
I need to put an end to it.

02:02.163 --> 02:03.414
An end?

02:05.416 --> 02:07.335
Hello, Father. This is Shin I-rang.

02:07.418 --> 02:09.796
I'm sorry, but could you
come over to my office?

02:09.879 --> 02:11.464
Yes, this is an emergency.

02:12.132 --> 02:13.133
What…

02:19.222 --> 02:20.431
Hello, Mother.

02:20.515 --> 02:21.891
Did you arrive?

02:21.975 --> 02:22.976
Which hospital is it?

02:23.768 --> 02:24.978
Oh, the thing is…

02:26.229 --> 02:29.107
He went to his office just fine.
I don't think you should worry.

02:29.732 --> 02:30.900
Where is his office?

02:32.235 --> 02:33.236
That,

02:34.154 --> 02:35.238
I don't know.

02:38.575 --> 02:39.617
Which hospital is it?

02:39.701 --> 02:41.953
COURTROOMS,
CIVIL MEDIATION CENTER, ANNEX

02:42.036 --> 02:44.831
- He went to his office.
- He did?

02:46.541 --> 02:48.251
That means he's not injured much.

02:48.751 --> 02:50.295
What a relief.

02:50.378 --> 02:54.048
Did I-rang give you his business card?

02:54.132 --> 02:55.008
What?

02:55.091 --> 02:56.718
No, he said he didn't have any yet.

02:59.554 --> 03:01.097
Oh, excuse me.

03:03.349 --> 03:05.727
I'm Attorney Shin I-rang's family.

03:06.436 --> 03:09.981
Do you perhaps know where his office is?

03:10.648 --> 03:11.649
I do.

03:13.693 --> 03:14.694
Here you go.

03:15.278 --> 03:16.279
Thank you.

03:17.614 --> 03:19.741
PRINCIPAL ATTORNEY SHIN I-RANG

03:22.035 --> 03:23.328
Okcheon Building?

03:29.876 --> 03:31.586
Shin I-rang is a total nutcase.

03:32.128 --> 03:33.463
We might win easily thanks to him.

03:37.634 --> 03:38.635
Prosecutor Kim?

03:39.427 --> 03:40.762
Long time no see, Na-hyun.

03:40.845 --> 03:43.223
What brings you to a civil trial,
Prosecutor Kim?

03:43.306 --> 03:45.975
I decided to stop by
because I was curious.

03:46.059 --> 03:47.185
What?

03:47.268 --> 03:48.394
A search and seizure?

03:51.147 --> 03:53.191
Okay. I'll be there soon.

03:55.235 --> 03:57.362
Are you raiding Cheongil Hospital?

03:58.112 --> 03:59.197
There's no reason to do so.

03:59.280 --> 04:00.531
A man died.

04:01.241 --> 04:03.743
An investigation will determine
whether there's a reason or not.

04:05.078 --> 04:06.079
See you again, Na-hyun.

04:11.584 --> 04:14.087
That darn prosecutor is
just as annoying as ever.

04:16.506 --> 04:18.299
I better try
persuading the plaintiff again.

04:18.383 --> 04:21.594
She shouldn't act recklessly
at least for her sick daughter.

04:28.476 --> 04:29.644
Is what I asked for ready?

04:30.270 --> 04:31.271
Yes, sir.

04:32.939 --> 04:35.441
GANGSTER PATIENT WHO ASSAULTED
MEDICAL STAFF FALSELY CLAIMS MALPRACTICE

04:36.484 --> 04:38.486
Let's seal the deal
while we have the upper hand.

04:38.569 --> 04:41.030
Send this to the reporters
and plant it among YouTubers.

04:41.781 --> 04:42.782
Yes, sir.

04:50.498 --> 04:52.458
I should've burned these from the start.

04:52.542 --> 04:54.711
This happened because I was such a softie.

04:56.963 --> 04:58.965
I know it's not my business,

04:59.048 --> 05:00.675
but what about the case?

05:01.926 --> 05:03.094
I'll continue on my own.

05:04.470 --> 05:06.055
I'd like you to pray for him

05:06.764 --> 05:08.683
so that he can rest in peace at least.

05:09.434 --> 05:11.811
Why don't we wait until he comes

05:11.894 --> 05:13.479
for the sake of your time together?

05:14.105 --> 05:17.191
I might be swayed if I see him.

05:18.026 --> 05:19.193
Are you sure about this?

05:21.321 --> 05:22.530
Let me do it myself.

05:34.792 --> 05:36.294
GANGSTER PATIENT WHO ASSAULTED
MEDICAL STAFF FALSELY CLAIMS MALPRACTICE

05:48.806 --> 05:50.641
WHAT WOULD YOU EXPECT
FROM A GANGSTER? LOL

05:50.725 --> 05:53.311
JI-WOO

06:09.535 --> 06:10.620
What the…

06:13.998 --> 06:15.166
Ji-woo!

06:16.459 --> 06:18.377
What's going on? What's wrong?

06:21.297 --> 06:24.175
SCUM IS BETTER OFF DEAD,
JUSTICE SERVED, NICE!

06:30.389 --> 06:31.390
Darn it.

06:43.528 --> 06:45.029
Leave the rest to me…

06:47.156 --> 06:48.157
and rest in peace.

06:53.621 --> 06:55.957
No! Not now!

07:17.061 --> 07:18.521
Mr. Shin?

07:19.647 --> 07:21.566
You anchovy head.

07:23.234 --> 07:25.111
Stop right this instant.

07:25.194 --> 07:27.780
You know nothing!
Who are you to meddle with it?

07:48.676 --> 07:50.094
I need to go to my daughter.

07:51.012 --> 07:53.389
Don't try to get in the way,
or I'll make you pay.

07:55.475 --> 07:57.393
How could you do this to the priest!

08:00.938 --> 08:03.900
Did you just hit me, lady?

08:04.484 --> 08:06.444
What? "Lady"?

08:07.612 --> 08:10.490
I worked my butt off
to raise and educate you,

08:10.573 --> 08:13.367
and you dare call me "lady"?

08:15.453 --> 08:16.579
Say that again.

08:16.662 --> 08:18.873
Say that again, brat.

08:19.707 --> 08:21.083
Run away.

08:21.667 --> 08:24.378
This man isn't your son.

08:24.462 --> 08:25.963
What?

08:33.429 --> 08:34.680
Shin I-rang!

08:53.533 --> 08:54.992
What…

08:55.076 --> 08:56.452
What is going on?

09:01.082 --> 09:02.083
Ji-woo.

09:07.672 --> 09:09.090
Ji-woo…

09:14.720 --> 09:15.763
So, are you saying

09:16.347 --> 09:19.183
that this talisman summoned a ghost,

09:20.184 --> 09:24.146
my son happened to see that ghost
after opening his law office here,

09:24.230 --> 09:28.109
and that very ghost is
the victim of the earlier trial,

09:28.192 --> 09:29.277
Lee Gang-pung?

09:30.236 --> 09:31.237
That's right.

09:37.827 --> 09:41.455
Will I-rang come back
if we burn this talisman to ashes?

09:42.039 --> 09:43.040
Not now.

09:43.791 --> 09:45.167
He's possessed at the moment,

09:45.251 --> 09:48.087
so we don't know
what will happen if we do.

09:51.048 --> 09:53.342
LEE GANG-PUNG

10:01.267 --> 10:02.893
What happened?

10:09.066 --> 10:10.359
Help me, Mr. Attorney.

10:10.443 --> 10:11.485
I don't want to.

10:11.569 --> 10:14.322
I get that you're a ghost,
but have some shame.

10:14.405 --> 10:16.365
After all that you did,
you want my help again?

10:17.033 --> 10:18.326
This will be the last time.

10:18.409 --> 10:19.744
Go away.

10:19.827 --> 10:22.038
You just wouldn't listen
when I talk to you nicely.

10:23.497 --> 10:24.498
Ji-woo is sick!

10:34.550 --> 10:36.135
She read that article about my past.

10:37.303 --> 10:38.304
It must've shocked her.

10:39.430 --> 10:42.725
She clutched her stomach in pain
and passed out.

10:42.808 --> 10:45.394
Why did you save it until now?
You should've told me right away!

10:47.480 --> 10:48.606
Geez.

10:54.904 --> 10:56.113
Darn it.

11:07.375 --> 11:08.584
Can you take me to Sadang-dong?

11:08.668 --> 11:10.086
- Sure, get in.
- Okay.

11:14.423 --> 11:16.050
- Taking off.
- Okay.

11:36.529 --> 11:37.988
There! The right one.

11:38.072 --> 11:41.325
- Zero-five-two-five and star.
- Zero-five-two-five, star.

11:44.286 --> 11:46.247
There. In her room.

11:47.873 --> 11:49.083
Ji-woo.

11:49.166 --> 11:51.460
Ji-woo! Wake up.

11:57.174 --> 11:58.509
What… Where did he go?

12:01.345 --> 12:02.471
What's going on?

12:02.555 --> 12:04.181
Did you see a taxi here?

12:06.976 --> 12:08.769
Did you perhaps drive here?

12:35.588 --> 12:36.630
Get the doors, please.

12:46.432 --> 12:48.142
<i>Patient, can you hear me?</i>

13:25.554 --> 13:26.597
Ji-woo.

13:29.725 --> 13:30.726
Ji-woo.

13:33.187 --> 13:34.939
She had acute stomach cramps.

13:35.439 --> 13:36.607
She's okay now.

13:43.239 --> 13:44.823
Mom's here.

13:50.955 --> 13:51.956
I'm sorry.

13:52.665 --> 13:56.001
I had no idea his past would be an issue.

13:56.585 --> 14:00.381
Now, the defense will keep
pouncing on Mr. Lee's character.

14:01.090 --> 14:02.800
To deal with them,

14:02.883 --> 14:04.510
I need to know about him.

14:05.177 --> 14:07.388
I mean, everything about him
including his past.

14:09.265 --> 14:12.142
The first time I met him was 20 years ago.

14:13.018 --> 14:14.520
Where do I hang it?

14:14.603 --> 14:15.980
Over here, please.

14:16.063 --> 14:17.106
- Here?
- Yes.

14:17.189 --> 14:18.857
<i>I went to Cheongju Prison</i>

14:18.941 --> 14:21.735
<i>with my church people</i>
<i>to hold a Christmas service there.</i>

14:22.444 --> 14:25.781
<i>Gang-pung helped me make a Christmas tree.</i>

14:28.325 --> 14:31.036
He made foolish decisions
and became a gangster,

14:31.579 --> 14:33.706
but he reflected on his wrongdoings,

14:33.789 --> 14:36.041
turned himself in, and went to prison.

14:42.172 --> 14:44.008
VICTIM OF MALPRACTICE IN LEGAL BATTLE
WAS ONCE A GANGSTER

14:49.805 --> 14:51.515
I think that's enough.

14:53.142 --> 14:54.894
Let's go.

14:59.857 --> 15:02.234
You should be with Ji-woo for now.

15:02.735 --> 15:05.529
I'll do what I can
to prepare for the trial.

15:05.613 --> 15:06.739
Okay.

15:06.822 --> 15:09.450
- Attorney Shin.
- Yes?

15:09.533 --> 15:12.161
How did you enter my house, though?

15:12.870 --> 15:15.372
And how did you know that Ji-woo was sick?

15:16.332 --> 15:17.374
Oh, that…

15:18.208 --> 15:21.587
I went there
to get your signature on something

15:21.670 --> 15:24.131
and found Ji-woo unconscious.

15:24.214 --> 15:25.215
The door…

15:26.342 --> 15:28.135
The door was open.

15:29.178 --> 15:32.431
I wonder why the door was open.

15:35.809 --> 15:36.936
Then,

15:37.019 --> 15:40.230
why did you suddenly speak in a dialect
during the trial?

15:45.444 --> 15:48.238
I'm also from the same darn region.

15:49.823 --> 15:52.952
I speak in my hometown dialect
when I get worked up.

15:55.454 --> 15:57.289
Ji-woo shouldn't be alone.

15:57.373 --> 15:58.707
Hurry inside now.

15:58.791 --> 16:01.418
Okay, I will.

16:01.502 --> 16:03.295
- Sure, sure thing.
- Bye.

16:06.090 --> 16:07.091
Look.

16:09.802 --> 16:10.803
Thank you.

16:10.886 --> 16:12.930
It wasn't for you.

16:15.474 --> 16:18.394
Stay here and join me later
when Ji-woo gets better.

16:19.561 --> 16:20.896
Let's work on our next plan.

16:21.438 --> 16:22.439
Okay.

16:44.586 --> 16:45.587
Attorney Han.

16:50.175 --> 16:51.176
Attorney Han?

16:52.970 --> 16:53.971
Hello.

16:56.181 --> 16:57.516
You didn't leave.

16:58.434 --> 16:59.435
How is the girl?

17:00.310 --> 17:03.063
She still has a fever,
but she's stable now.

17:04.982 --> 17:07.359
You look a little pale.

17:08.027 --> 17:09.028
Are you okay?

17:10.487 --> 17:11.488
I'm okay.

17:18.037 --> 17:19.204
Is she not feeling well?

17:46.648 --> 17:47.649
Mom, I'm back.

17:50.152 --> 17:52.988
W-What is it this time? You're scaring me.

17:53.072 --> 17:54.198
Shin I-rang.

18:01.246 --> 18:02.664
Look me straight in the eye.

18:05.417 --> 18:08.087
It's scary every time you call me
by my full name.

18:09.338 --> 18:11.340
Did I do something wrong again?

18:17.805 --> 18:18.806
Goodness.

18:20.390 --> 18:21.725
Mom.

18:21.809 --> 18:23.519
This is a bit awkward.

18:23.602 --> 18:26.063
Can't you be on my case as usual?

18:26.688 --> 18:27.731
No way.

18:28.357 --> 18:31.318
I can't possibly mistreat my precious son.

18:31.902 --> 18:35.114
But we should be precise
with calculations.

18:39.451 --> 18:40.619
Let's see.

18:41.537 --> 18:43.497
COMMERCIAL LEASE AGREEMENT

18:45.332 --> 18:46.500
You found out?

18:47.000 --> 18:48.293
It was too easy.

18:48.877 --> 18:51.713
You opened a law office under your name.

18:51.797 --> 18:53.423
It was obvious where you got the money.

18:55.300 --> 18:57.052
Mom, the thing is--

18:57.136 --> 18:58.512
It's okay.

18:58.595 --> 19:02.307
Now that it turned out this way,
I'll consider it an investment.

19:02.975 --> 19:04.226
Stamp your fingerprint here.

19:04.309 --> 19:05.310
What…

19:05.394 --> 19:07.521
HALF OF SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE
BELONGS TO MOM

19:07.604 --> 19:08.689
Half?

19:08.772 --> 19:11.525
Sure we're immediate family,
but this isn't fair.

19:11.608 --> 19:13.068
Should I own it all, then?

19:15.988 --> 19:17.364
Fine.

19:17.447 --> 19:19.074
I don't have an ink pad, though.

19:29.501 --> 19:30.919
MOM: PARK GYEONG-HWA
SON: SHIN I-RANG

19:31.003 --> 19:32.629
There you go.

19:33.672 --> 19:36.175
It's nearby, so have your meals here.

19:36.675 --> 19:37.843
You can drive…

19:38.969 --> 19:40.095
There's a car?

19:44.141 --> 19:47.603
SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE

19:48.520 --> 19:49.563
Here you go.

19:50.147 --> 19:51.356
Its oil needs to be changed.

19:52.149 --> 19:55.319
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

20:01.033 --> 20:05.037
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

20:10.751 --> 20:12.794
- Geez, that startled me!
- Oh, my goodness!

20:14.755 --> 20:16.798
Can't you just show up in an ordinary way?

20:16.882 --> 20:18.717
I freaked out even more.

20:19.468 --> 20:20.886
Want me to knock or something?

20:20.969 --> 20:23.931
To open the door and put the seat belt on?

20:24.681 --> 20:25.891
Keep your cool, I-rang.

20:26.558 --> 20:28.060
You're not dealing with a human.

20:30.604 --> 20:31.688
Anyway,

20:32.481 --> 20:34.650
shouldn't we find Nurse Oh Jin-suk?

20:35.567 --> 20:38.070
No one will believe us without her.

20:39.988 --> 20:41.823
- I found her.
- What?

20:41.907 --> 20:43.742
I got a call from the detective agency.

20:45.494 --> 20:48.830
<i>Ms. Oh is a divorced mom</i>
<i>raising her child alone.</i>

20:50.040 --> 20:53.001
<i>She was so poor that when Lee Jeong-seok</i>
<i>offered money to silence her,</i>

20:53.669 --> 20:54.920
<i>she couldn't turn it down.</i>

20:55.504 --> 20:56.713
Nurse Oh Jin-suk?

21:10.435 --> 21:11.770
A mom can do anything…

21:14.564 --> 21:15.774
for her child.

21:19.653 --> 21:20.654
But is that really

21:22.364 --> 21:23.657
for your child?

21:25.867 --> 21:26.868
Hi, guys.

21:33.417 --> 21:34.751
Why? What is it?

21:38.088 --> 21:39.089
What's going on?

21:41.800 --> 21:42.801
What is it?

21:45.345 --> 21:47.306
FOLLOW YOUR DAD TO PRISON
YOUR DAD IS A LIAR

21:47.389 --> 21:49.349
LEAVE OUR SCHOOL!
DID A GHOST TAKE YOUR DAD?

21:55.689 --> 21:56.898
I-RANG'S DAD IS A CRIMINAL!

21:56.982 --> 21:58.358
<i>I know it all too well</i>

21:59.359 --> 22:01.111
<i>how devastating it is for a child…</i>

22:02.070 --> 22:03.071
CORRUPT PROSECUTOR

22:03.155 --> 22:05.365
<i>…when they realize the dirty truth</i>

22:06.491 --> 22:07.951
behind the privileges they've had.

22:08.660 --> 22:10.245
That's not the case for Jun-seo.

22:13.248 --> 22:14.249
He's too young

22:15.500 --> 22:16.793
to know anything.

22:18.712 --> 22:19.713
All right.

22:20.756 --> 22:23.550
Let's say you'll manage
to keep him in the dark somehow.

22:24.593 --> 22:27.220
- But have you been at ease?
- It's too late now.

22:30.265 --> 22:32.517
Once you die, you're dead for good.

22:33.060 --> 22:34.478
It's all over.

22:34.561 --> 22:35.729
It's not over.

22:38.857 --> 22:40.358
There's another person dying.

22:41.818 --> 22:43.153
What do you mean?

22:43.737 --> 22:44.946
Mr. Lee Gang-pung's daughter.

22:46.698 --> 22:48.033
You've seen her at the hospital.

22:54.122 --> 22:55.624
Make it quick and come back out, okay?

22:55.707 --> 22:56.958
I have an exam tomorrow.

22:58.085 --> 23:00.712
Take it easy with your exams.

23:01.296 --> 23:03.090
Stop joking around.

23:03.173 --> 23:04.800
Okay, my kiddo.

23:05.759 --> 23:07.594
My surgery will be over in a jiffy.

23:08.804 --> 23:10.514
Good luck.

23:10.597 --> 23:11.598
Don't worry.

23:14.601 --> 23:16.853
- See you.
- See you later.

23:19.356 --> 23:20.982
<i>Since her dad died,</i>

23:21.066 --> 23:23.985
<i>she cooped herself in her room</i>
<i>and barely ate anything.</i>

23:25.487 --> 23:28.448
<i>She ended up passing out</i>
<i>and got sent to the ER.</i>

23:32.911 --> 23:35.247
Her healthy dad died overnight.

23:37.165 --> 23:38.166
It'd be odd

23:39.501 --> 23:40.585
if she were okay.

23:46.133 --> 23:47.259
Now that you know,

23:48.802 --> 23:49.803
please testify.

23:51.263 --> 23:53.807
You're the only one
who can tell the truth.

23:55.225 --> 23:56.226
So, please…

23:58.854 --> 24:00.230
reveal the truth.

24:04.776 --> 24:05.777
I can't do it.

24:08.238 --> 24:10.574
That man is going to make us pay.

24:14.703 --> 24:17.831
What else haven't you told me
other than Oh Jin-suk?

24:18.790 --> 24:22.294
I'm asking if the search and seizure
may find anything against us.

24:22.878 --> 24:25.547
An EMR, for example.

24:25.630 --> 24:27.048
EMR…

24:27.132 --> 24:28.133
What's that?

24:28.842 --> 24:30.343
Electronic Medical Record.

24:30.427 --> 24:32.762
It's the mainframe
of a hospital's computer room.

24:32.846 --> 24:35.098
All surgical records are stored in it.

24:36.141 --> 24:37.142
Anesthesia doctor?

24:37.225 --> 24:40.270
<i>Does it mean it has a record</i>
<i>of my heart rate during the surgery?</i>

24:40.353 --> 24:41.354
<i>That's right.</i>

24:41.438 --> 24:43.648
<i>Only if we find that hard disk,</i>

24:43.732 --> 24:46.610
<i>we can perfectly prove</i>
<i>against the doctor's claim</i>

24:46.693 --> 24:48.403
<i>that you died of a heart attack.</i>

24:49.654 --> 24:51.698
You should be called Attorney Romantic.

24:51.781 --> 24:54.284
Did you graduate from med school too?

24:54.367 --> 24:55.368
What a playlist.

24:55.452 --> 24:56.786
- What?
- What?

24:58.622 --> 24:59.998
I didn't know until today.

25:00.790 --> 25:01.791
<i>Mr. Attorney.</i>

25:05.378 --> 25:07.214
They submitted
a fabricated record to court.

25:08.924 --> 25:10.050
Search through the EMR.

25:10.884 --> 25:13.303
The original should be
in the operating room's computer.

25:15.472 --> 25:17.265
Ms. Oh Jin-suk told me.

25:17.349 --> 25:18.808
Oh, I see.

25:18.892 --> 25:21.102
Anyway, it'll be game over
with that, right?

25:22.062 --> 25:23.855
But where is it?

25:23.939 --> 25:25.148
That's the question.

25:25.732 --> 25:27.234
When I asked the hospital for it,

25:27.317 --> 25:28.944
they said they recently got a new one.

25:29.027 --> 25:31.404
They got a new one?
What about the old one, then?

25:32.113 --> 25:33.114
They sold it.

25:33.198 --> 25:34.199
Sold it?

25:34.950 --> 25:36.993
So, I made an anonymous report.

25:37.077 --> 25:39.079
The prosecution should've
started investigating by now.

25:39.162 --> 25:41.331
I'll check the surveillance footage
around the hospital.

25:41.414 --> 25:44.626
I need you to collect information
by the prosecutor in charge.

25:45.126 --> 25:46.127
Okay.

25:49.422 --> 25:50.715
<i>From what I heard,</i>

25:50.799 --> 25:53.677
the prosecution got an anonymous report
about the EMR.

25:54.261 --> 25:56.179
That's why they started investigating.

25:56.930 --> 25:59.766
We're about to get busted
thanks to some idiot.

25:59.849 --> 26:00.850
What did you say, woman?

26:00.934 --> 26:02.894
Watch what you say, Attorney Han.

26:02.978 --> 26:05.605
I can't chime in with improbable lies.

26:05.689 --> 26:07.774
Are you kidding me?

26:07.857 --> 26:09.359
- Han Na-hyun.
- Yes?

26:09.442 --> 26:10.568
You're dismissed.

26:12.153 --> 26:13.738
I'm in charge of this case.

26:15.365 --> 26:16.408
You heard me.

26:19.119 --> 26:22.122
TAEBAEK LAW FIRM

26:28.211 --> 26:30.213
Gosh, I'm lost for words.

26:31.339 --> 26:32.632
What's with her?

26:36.386 --> 26:37.470
Geez.

26:55.947 --> 26:56.990
What…

26:57.073 --> 26:58.325
What's wrong?

27:04.956 --> 27:06.041
I understand.

27:06.833 --> 27:09.002
You killed a man.
No wonder you're losing your mind.

27:09.085 --> 27:10.086
Kill…

27:11.504 --> 27:14.341
Kill him? Who do you mean?

27:14.424 --> 27:17.469
I did speak to you kindly with honorifics,

27:18.553 --> 27:19.637
but we're not friends.

27:19.721 --> 27:20.722
Wait.

27:21.222 --> 27:23.266
I offered that nurse money as you advised.

27:23.808 --> 27:27.187
I handed over the EMR to you
because you said you'd take care of it.

27:29.064 --> 27:30.065
I…

27:31.399 --> 27:33.818
even recorded our conversations,

27:34.903 --> 27:35.904
sir…

27:40.450 --> 27:41.451
So what?

27:42.369 --> 27:43.828
Who's going to listen to it?

27:44.829 --> 27:46.122
The judges?

27:46.790 --> 27:49.834
Will you let them know
that you messed up and killed a man,

27:49.918 --> 27:52.504
and that your attorney helped you
get away with it?

27:52.587 --> 27:54.506
- No, that's not it.
- Hey!

28:02.555 --> 28:04.641
When someone cleans up after your mess,

28:04.724 --> 28:06.226
you should be grateful

28:07.560 --> 28:10.146
if you ever see reason, okay?

28:18.071 --> 28:20.490
Consider yourself blessed
to have Attorney Han defend you.

28:25.203 --> 28:27.997
Han Na-hyun would even risk her life
to win a trial.

28:48.059 --> 28:49.394
CONTACTS

28:49.477 --> 28:51.104
PROSECUTOR KIM HYEON-U

28:51.187 --> 28:52.355
A hospital computer?

28:54.357 --> 28:56.025
We don't service such computers.

28:56.860 --> 29:00.613
Then, could there be a place
that services used hospital computers?

29:00.697 --> 29:01.823
Probably.

29:04.909 --> 29:05.910
An informant?

29:06.745 --> 29:09.372
I know you tried
to find this anonymous informant.

29:10.248 --> 29:12.834
If they're going to testify,
we have the right to know who it is.

29:12.917 --> 29:14.252
I don't know who it is.

29:14.878 --> 29:17.672
The person used a public phone,
and no CCTV cameras were nearby.

29:20.049 --> 29:23.470
Based on the report,
it's highly likely to be an insider.

29:23.553 --> 29:26.598
Don't you have anyone in mind?
Or maybe the doctor said something.

29:27.807 --> 29:28.975
No.

29:29.058 --> 29:31.978
Hospitals are where
random people come and go.

29:32.061 --> 29:33.813
He said he couldn't specify anyone.

29:37.233 --> 29:39.068
INVESTIGATOR LEE
I THINK WE FOUND IT

29:39.152 --> 29:40.445
Just a moment.

29:44.866 --> 29:46.659
Let me go to the bathroom.

29:46.743 --> 29:47.744
Sure.

30:08.264 --> 30:09.432
What's wrong?

30:10.642 --> 30:11.810
I dropped it in the bathroom.

30:13.061 --> 30:15.063
I have to make an urgent call.
Can I use your phone?

30:15.146 --> 30:16.147
Of course.

30:30.453 --> 30:32.372
"Saenara Used Appliances."

30:47.011 --> 30:48.221
MR. YANG DO-GYEONG

30:49.138 --> 30:50.682
Hello, Attorney Yang.

30:50.765 --> 30:52.308
Did you take care of the computer?

30:52.392 --> 30:54.602
It will cross the sea

30:54.686 --> 30:57.272
to meet its new owner tonight.

30:57.856 --> 30:59.440
Did you get rid of the hard disk?

30:59.524 --> 31:01.192
Of course, I burned it and threw it out.

31:01.943 --> 31:04.445
The prosecution is sniffing around.
Be careful.

31:04.529 --> 31:05.780
Okay, goodbye.

31:11.870 --> 31:13.329
CHEONGIL HOSPITAL

31:13.413 --> 31:15.915
I'd be crazy
if I got rid of this nice safety net.

31:18.543 --> 31:20.795
Let's go to the warehouse.

31:28.344 --> 31:29.345
Where did you find it?

31:30.763 --> 31:32.473
We received pictures from our source.

31:34.142 --> 31:35.768
They were taken last night.

31:36.436 --> 31:38.688
I asked the hospital,
and they said it was their device.

31:39.397 --> 31:40.523
Where's the location?

31:40.607 --> 31:42.901
Incheon, and the owner is Cho Gi-cheol.

31:44.569 --> 31:45.570
Incheon.

31:47.280 --> 31:48.656
Should we request a search warrant?

31:49.699 --> 31:51.951
It'll be too late if we wait for it.
Let's head there now.

31:59.250 --> 32:00.251
Mr. Attorney.

32:01.127 --> 32:03.171
Saenara Used Appliances has the computer.

32:03.254 --> 32:05.381
- Saenara Used Appliances?
- I saw them talking.

32:20.313 --> 32:22.523
KANG HA-NA
SUPREME PROSECUTORS' OFFICE

32:29.364 --> 32:30.365
KIM HAE-YEONG

32:30.448 --> 32:31.449
<i>Attached is the info</i>

32:31.532 --> 32:33.117
<i>on Saenara Used Appliances and its owner.</i>

32:33.201 --> 32:34.452
CRIMINAL RECORDS CHECK REPORT

32:34.535 --> 32:35.703
BUSINESS LICENSE

32:41.960 --> 32:43.002
Great work today! Thank you!

32:47.298 --> 32:49.550
You didn't have to come
all the way here, I-rang.

32:50.218 --> 32:52.428
You know I played a surgeon role

32:52.512 --> 32:55.056
in the SBS weekend drama,
<i>Doctors</i>, a year ago.

32:55.139 --> 32:58.810
I didn't have any lines, but I got
quite a lot of blood on my hands.

32:58.893 --> 33:00.728
Oh, you did.

33:01.437 --> 33:02.689
I was in a rush.

33:03.606 --> 33:05.817
Anyway, we need to find
a computer mainframe

33:05.900 --> 33:08.820
a bit bigger than a normal computer
with a blue sticker on it.

33:08.903 --> 33:10.863
I see. Don't you worry.
You can count on me.

33:10.947 --> 33:12.448
- Okay.
- Let's go.

33:14.117 --> 33:15.118
Off we go.

33:30.550 --> 33:32.844
SAENARA USED APPLIANCES

33:35.221 --> 33:36.264
We're here.

33:49.277 --> 33:50.278
Excuse me…

34:04.000 --> 34:05.710
What are you going to do with that?

34:06.544 --> 34:08.337
I doubt any workers are still here.

34:08.421 --> 34:10.673
- Then?
- I'll just sneak in and get the computer.

34:11.799 --> 34:14.093
Can you keep watch on that side?

34:14.177 --> 34:15.094
Okay.

34:15.678 --> 34:16.804
Hey…

34:17.305 --> 34:18.931
This makes me feel uneasy.

34:29.567 --> 34:30.568
Look.

34:30.651 --> 34:32.070
I think you should be careful.

34:32.862 --> 34:35.031
I know the owner here.

34:35.615 --> 34:36.866
You know him?

34:36.949 --> 34:39.535
He used to be my boss
back when I was young and stupid.

34:40.078 --> 34:41.746
Are you saying he's a gangster?

34:42.663 --> 34:43.748
He was vicious.

34:44.373 --> 34:47.085
<i>He beat up whoever displeased him</i>
<i>to a pulp.</i>

34:47.752 --> 34:49.837
<i>Every time, he sang the same song.</i>

34:52.465 --> 34:54.634
A gangster exports used appliances
for a living?

34:55.885 --> 34:57.845
Maybe he turned over a new leaf.

34:58.513 --> 35:00.223
Even a dog passing by would laugh.

35:03.559 --> 35:06.395
He started trafficking drugs 20 years ago.

35:06.479 --> 35:07.772
What? Drugs?

35:16.072 --> 35:17.824
Does that mean
this place isn't a warehouse,

35:17.907 --> 35:19.659
but the den of a drug syndicate?

35:21.160 --> 35:23.579
Sure seems like it with those guys around.

35:24.205 --> 35:27.625
- What's going on?
- Who the heck is it?

35:28.668 --> 35:30.878
You should've told me that sooner!

35:30.962 --> 35:33.548
Please don't save important information!

35:34.132 --> 35:35.925
I'd been meaning to tell you.

35:36.008 --> 35:37.677
I-rang!

35:37.760 --> 35:40.763
These guys seem very angry!

35:41.305 --> 35:42.306
Get them!

35:42.390 --> 35:43.808
What's going on?

35:48.187 --> 35:49.230
Get them!

35:58.990 --> 36:00.199
Move over.

36:06.372 --> 36:07.582
Two people aren't enough.

36:09.542 --> 36:10.793
- Just a moment.
- What?

36:10.877 --> 36:13.045
Where are you going, I-rang!

36:20.344 --> 36:21.554
Help out!

36:21.637 --> 36:22.889
I'm sorry!

36:24.473 --> 36:27.059
I-rang, I'm doing what I can!

36:27.643 --> 36:28.811
I didn't mean you.

36:29.896 --> 36:30.897
Bong-su, over here.

36:47.914 --> 36:50.499
I-rang, hold this position.

36:50.583 --> 36:52.376
I'll go find the computer, okay?

36:52.460 --> 36:53.753
But…

36:54.337 --> 36:55.338
Me too!

36:56.839 --> 36:59.967
So what if you find it?
We have no way out of here!

37:13.397 --> 37:15.274
You got brains in those heads of yours?

37:15.358 --> 37:17.693
There are windows on the side!

37:17.777 --> 37:18.736
- Yes, sir!
- The windows!

37:18.819 --> 37:19.695
Get the windows.

37:19.779 --> 37:21.614
Damn morons.

37:39.465 --> 37:41.467
What are you waiting for?
They're about to come in!

37:41.550 --> 37:42.802
Oh, here are the computers.

37:42.885 --> 37:44.595
Hold on. A bit bigger. A blue sticker.

37:44.679 --> 37:46.305
A bit bigger. A blue sticker.

37:47.181 --> 37:48.224
Outta my way.

37:51.143 --> 37:54.480
Gosh. A bit bigger. A blue sticker. A bit…

37:58.401 --> 37:59.610
A blue sticker.

37:59.694 --> 38:00.778
I found it!

38:04.448 --> 38:08.828
I-rang, I found the computer,
but the hard disk is missing!

38:09.412 --> 38:10.913
It doesn't matter!

38:11.747 --> 38:13.499
Find a hole in the wall or something!

38:34.145 --> 38:35.354
I found it!

38:35.438 --> 38:36.856
I found it here.

38:36.939 --> 38:37.940
Really?

38:44.572 --> 38:46.073
Where's the computer?

38:46.949 --> 38:49.368
Computer? No, I found a dog hole.

38:50.786 --> 38:52.121
W-What?

38:52.872 --> 38:54.874
You told me
not to save important information.

38:55.750 --> 38:57.918
The "what" you found
is the important part!

38:58.627 --> 39:00.880
You darn dog-hole ghost!

39:00.963 --> 39:02.673
Darn dog hole?

39:07.803 --> 39:08.804
I mean a dog hole.

39:14.560 --> 39:15.770
Where are they?

39:15.853 --> 39:17.146
Let's go. Hurry.

39:51.472 --> 39:53.015
I'm from the Prosecutors' Office.

39:55.351 --> 39:56.394
That woman…

39:56.936 --> 39:59.146
I hear you're keeping important evidence.

39:59.730 --> 40:01.524
KANG HA-NA
SUPREME PROSECUTORS' OFFICE

40:01.607 --> 40:04.151
Did you buy that online or what?

40:05.736 --> 40:08.364
Boys, she claims herself
to be a prosecutor.

40:11.158 --> 40:12.243
Cho Gi-cheol.

40:12.326 --> 40:15.329
You were born on February 11, 1979.

40:15.413 --> 40:17.373
Your hometown is
Sasaeng-dong, Chungcheongnam-do.

40:18.082 --> 40:20.626
Your mother is dead,
and your father is missing.

40:20.709 --> 40:23.087
You have seven assault convictions
and two fraud convictions.

40:24.797 --> 40:26.173
You are beyond saving.

40:27.091 --> 40:28.092
What's your deal?

40:29.427 --> 40:31.595
What are you saying?

40:33.848 --> 40:36.934
What you did just now is
assault and obstruction of justice.

40:37.518 --> 40:39.353
Add concealing crucial evidence to that,

40:40.229 --> 40:42.022
and you'll be in the slammer for a while.

40:43.190 --> 40:45.192
I'm going to pile on
the punishment, you see.

40:53.159 --> 40:54.452
Fine, I'll let you check.

40:57.329 --> 40:58.330
Boys, open it up.

41:09.008 --> 41:10.885
Attorney Han is here to find

41:11.802 --> 41:13.637
what the doctor hid?

41:13.721 --> 41:15.347
Isn't she on his side?

41:19.560 --> 41:21.854
I know. This is strange.

41:22.730 --> 41:23.731
Wow.

41:25.191 --> 41:26.984
It's the 1991 Grandeur box-type.

41:27.568 --> 41:30.446
Wow, it's even got authentic interior.

41:31.572 --> 41:32.698
This is Cho Gi-cheol's car.

41:32.781 --> 41:35.159
There's a secret space under the seat.

41:36.202 --> 41:37.203
A secret space?

41:38.037 --> 41:39.079
What? What did you say?

41:42.166 --> 41:44.793
I-rang! What are you doing?

41:45.294 --> 41:47.129
I-rang, don't do that.

41:47.713 --> 41:48.923
Oh, geez.

41:49.006 --> 41:50.549
This is not good.

41:50.633 --> 41:51.717
What are you doing?

41:52.510 --> 41:53.511
I found it.

41:53.594 --> 41:55.179
What on earth?

41:55.262 --> 41:57.431
How did you know where it was?

41:59.350 --> 42:01.685
It's a business secret.

42:02.478 --> 42:04.146
What? You're scaring me.

42:04.230 --> 42:05.814
Anyway, let's get out of here.

42:07.149 --> 42:08.275
Hold on.

42:15.824 --> 42:16.909
Actual drugs.

42:46.647 --> 42:50.943
Oh, dear. We got caught. What should I do?

42:52.069 --> 42:53.070
Get her.

42:53.153 --> 42:54.530
The prosecution knows

42:55.281 --> 42:56.407
that I'm here.

42:56.490 --> 42:59.535
I don't care if she's a prosecutor.
Get her.

43:25.686 --> 43:26.729
What the heck?

43:27.479 --> 43:28.731
Isn't that my car?

43:43.412 --> 43:45.372
Attorney Han, are you okay?

43:46.373 --> 43:47.374
I'm screwed.

43:47.958 --> 43:48.959
Attorney?

43:49.668 --> 43:50.669
Not a prosecutor?

43:51.629 --> 43:53.213
Are you or are you not?

43:54.590 --> 43:56.759
I-rang!

43:58.761 --> 44:00.054
What?

44:00.638 --> 44:03.015
What is this cute trick
you're pulling all together?

44:03.557 --> 44:04.558
Boys!

44:05.726 --> 44:07.227
Get them all.

44:08.520 --> 44:09.563
I-rang.

44:27.581 --> 44:28.666
Wait.

44:31.835 --> 44:32.836
Wait a minute!

44:36.423 --> 44:38.842
Whoever is up there,
I know you're watching!

44:39.343 --> 44:41.387
Please help me out once more!

44:41.470 --> 44:44.181
Give me strength just this one last time!

44:51.563 --> 44:54.233
Why didn't you just set this place on fire

44:54.316 --> 44:56.485
instead of smashing it all?

44:56.568 --> 44:57.569
You're really

44:59.113 --> 45:02.074
making things exhausting!

45:02.866 --> 45:03.867
Darn.

45:04.368 --> 45:05.828
Turn the music on.

45:05.911 --> 45:06.912
Yes, sir.

45:21.135 --> 45:23.137
Put that thing down before you regret it.

45:26.348 --> 45:27.349
I don't want to.

45:28.392 --> 45:31.437
Which one should I beat up first?

45:31.520 --> 45:34.523
Make a guess

45:34.606 --> 45:35.607
or not!

45:36.150 --> 45:37.151
Okay,

45:37.651 --> 45:38.861
the first target is

45:39.653 --> 45:40.654
the girl who fooled me.

45:44.741 --> 45:45.742
Are you okay?

45:48.412 --> 45:49.663
This is unfair.

45:50.831 --> 45:52.082
I came here first,

45:52.583 --> 45:54.209
so I should also take
the beating first, no?

45:55.752 --> 45:57.713
Is that your wish?

45:58.213 --> 46:01.550
Punk, your wish is
going to come true today.

46:02.801 --> 46:05.512
Turn up the volume!

46:05.596 --> 46:08.932
How disappointing of you!
I hear you're good and kind!

46:09.433 --> 46:12.060
Why are you sitting back
and watching, huh?

46:13.020 --> 46:14.021
Oh, come on!

46:24.364 --> 46:25.365
This song…

46:27.493 --> 46:30.287
It's a happy moment. Happy days.

46:31.079 --> 46:32.915
Smile. Smile, you punks.

46:33.999 --> 46:35.834
It's a happy day!

46:37.461 --> 46:39.087
<i>When they're faced with someone they hate</i>

46:39.171 --> 46:41.215
<i>or something that causes rage,</i>

46:42.007 --> 46:43.550
<i>the possibility of possession increases.</i>

47:01.568 --> 47:03.195
Oh, your cheeks are burning.

47:08.325 --> 47:09.409
Are you done swinging?

47:10.035 --> 47:11.036
Is it my turn now?

47:11.787 --> 47:14.248
What's this strange sense of déjà vu?

47:15.374 --> 47:17.334
- Who are you?
- Me?

47:18.919 --> 47:21.755
I'm gangster attorney, Lee Gang-pung!

47:23.298 --> 47:24.716
What the heck are you saying?

47:25.926 --> 47:26.927
Stop joking around.

47:27.761 --> 47:29.888
They're gangsters,
and they even have drugs.

47:30.931 --> 47:32.349
Don't worry, my dear.

47:32.933 --> 47:34.434
I'll save you soon.

47:34.518 --> 47:35.811
Okay?

47:37.646 --> 47:38.897
"My dear"?

47:38.981 --> 47:42.609
We might need a whole hospital
to accommodate you all.

47:42.693 --> 47:44.695
Or a funeral hall can be another option.

47:44.778 --> 47:47.573
Why you damn nutjob…

47:50.576 --> 47:51.910
Trying to catch a fly?

48:06.550 --> 48:08.468
Where do you think you're going?

48:09.636 --> 48:11.179
Go on! Attack him!

48:14.850 --> 48:17.102
What in the world?

48:26.778 --> 48:28.614
I-rang!

48:28.697 --> 48:29.740
Wait.

48:29.823 --> 48:30.824
Don't leave us!

48:30.907 --> 48:31.992
Oh, no!

48:34.620 --> 48:36.496
No, that's enough!

49:01.688 --> 49:03.148
You're dead meat!

49:19.956 --> 49:20.957
What the…

49:22.959 --> 49:24.044
Push!

49:31.009 --> 49:32.177
Darn.

49:47.693 --> 49:49.277
Attack him. Get in there!

50:10.549 --> 50:11.842
Spare me!

50:20.892 --> 50:21.935
I don't want to.

50:22.436 --> 50:25.397
SAENARA USED APPLIANCES

50:44.833 --> 50:47.043
I-rang!

50:47.586 --> 50:50.088
What… Can you stay with him?

50:50.172 --> 50:51.381
I'll go bring people.

50:54.217 --> 50:55.218
Mr. Shin.

50:55.802 --> 50:58.180
Attorney Shin, can you hear me?

50:58.847 --> 50:59.848
Attorney Shin!

51:07.439 --> 51:09.816
CHEONGIL HOSPITAL

51:32.464 --> 51:34.090
<i>Attorney Han, are you okay?</i>

51:47.854 --> 51:48.855
Are you okay?

51:50.816 --> 51:51.858
This is unfair.

51:53.026 --> 51:54.694
I came here first,

51:54.778 --> 51:56.613
so I should also take
the beating first, no?

52:10.919 --> 52:12.170
- Let's go inside.
- Yes, sir.

52:12.671 --> 52:14.339
Get the nearby surveillance footage first.

52:14.422 --> 52:15.423
Yes, sir.

52:18.510 --> 52:22.180
<i>The man who was recently criticized</i>
<i>for playing the victim</i>

52:22.264 --> 52:25.767
<i>turns out to have been murdered</i>
<i>by the doctor in charge.</i>

52:25.851 --> 52:29.020
<i>The police have proved the doctor's murder</i>

52:29.104 --> 52:31.982
<i>based on the hospital computer's hard disk</i>

52:32.065 --> 52:34.734
<i>and the testimony</i>
<i>of the nurse who witnessed it.</i>

52:34.818 --> 52:35.819
<i>Meanwhile, they're--</i>

52:54.588 --> 52:58.592
HAN SO-HYUN

53:01.678 --> 53:04.598
COURT OF KOREA

53:07.976 --> 53:08.977
EFFORT ALWAYS PAYS OFF

53:09.060 --> 53:10.478
ATTORNEY SEO IN-GYU DUBBED "KING"

53:16.359 --> 53:18.194
A LAWYER THAT PEOPLE WANT TO EMPLOY!
A LAWYER THAT PEOPLE BELIEVE IN!

53:18.278 --> 53:19.487
I WANT TO BE A LAWYER
THAT ALWAYS WINS!

53:19.571 --> 53:20.614
I MUST WIN EVERY TIME!

53:25.744 --> 53:26.745
WON
WON

53:27.329 --> 53:29.539
WON, WON, WON,
WON, WON, WON

53:32.667 --> 53:35.420
WON, WON, WON,
WON, WON, WON

54:06.534 --> 54:10.956
LOST

54:12.207 --> 54:13.416
- Mr. Attorney.
- Hello.

54:22.217 --> 54:23.259
How is Ji-woo?

54:47.659 --> 54:48.910
Hi, Ji-woo.

54:50.537 --> 54:52.455
I'm Attorney Shin I-rang.

54:53.415 --> 54:56.418
We met briefly at the hospital, remember?

55:00.380 --> 55:01.381
Is it still…

55:02.924 --> 55:04.384
too hard for you?

55:17.272 --> 55:18.273
Ji-woo.

55:20.442 --> 55:21.651
Your dad…

55:23.945 --> 55:25.905
didn't die because of you.

55:27.866 --> 55:29.617
It's not your fault.

55:31.369 --> 55:33.997
So, don't blame yourself too much.

55:36.541 --> 55:38.501
What do you know, mister?

55:45.216 --> 55:46.217
I…

55:48.219 --> 55:49.596
can tell.

55:53.141 --> 55:54.642
What? You don't like it?

55:54.726 --> 55:56.561
Why are you picking at the food?

55:57.187 --> 55:58.354
It's nothing.

55:58.438 --> 56:01.107
No way. I can tell there's something.

56:01.608 --> 56:03.068
Come on and tell me.

56:03.651 --> 56:05.779
I couldn't sleep
because you snored too loudly.

56:06.362 --> 56:07.363
That's not good.

56:07.864 --> 56:11.076
My kiddo will have trouble getting tall
and studying if she can't sleep.

56:11.159 --> 56:14.245
This won't do.
I'll go see a doctor right away.

56:15.455 --> 56:16.998
It's all my fault.

56:19.542 --> 56:21.586
I heard snoring wasn't good
for your health,

56:23.171 --> 56:26.216
and I knew my dad
would do anything for me.

56:28.176 --> 56:30.470
If I just didn't say that,

56:31.721 --> 56:33.515
he wouldn't have died.

56:37.185 --> 56:38.478
No, Ji-woo.

56:41.314 --> 56:42.732
My death…

56:44.734 --> 56:46.694
is absolutely not your fault.

56:48.029 --> 56:49.864
The hospital and the doctor are to blame.

56:50.615 --> 56:54.077
Those in the wrong were all punished.

56:54.160 --> 56:55.161
So…

56:58.248 --> 56:59.707
So Ji-woo, please…

57:01.626 --> 57:02.627
go back

57:04.129 --> 57:05.505
to your usual bright self.

57:07.674 --> 57:08.967
Live happily…

57:10.969 --> 57:13.388
with your mom for me, okay?

57:15.849 --> 57:17.016
Okay, kiddo?

57:20.645 --> 57:21.646
Dad?

57:43.126 --> 57:44.127
Mom.

57:45.378 --> 57:47.046
I heard Dad's voice.

57:47.130 --> 57:48.131
What?

57:50.592 --> 57:54.262
I guess your dad is
always keeping by our side.

57:59.225 --> 58:02.645
Let's be brave

58:02.729 --> 58:05.023
and live happily, okay?

58:40.099 --> 58:41.142
Wait.

58:43.228 --> 58:46.147
Must we burn this talisman?

58:50.026 --> 58:52.529
He can just stay with us.

58:52.612 --> 58:56.032
He'll get to watch Ji-woo grow
and be of support to Min-ju.

58:56.115 --> 58:57.116
Attorney Shin.

58:57.200 --> 58:58.660
Why must he go?

58:59.410 --> 59:00.495
I should.

59:01.621 --> 59:03.414
I don't belong here.

59:11.172 --> 59:14.008
Thank you so much for everything.

59:21.266 --> 59:22.308
The pleasure is mine.

59:24.352 --> 59:25.353
Thank you.

59:29.857 --> 59:31.359
It was only for a short time,

59:32.944 --> 59:34.195
but I was happy.

59:36.614 --> 59:37.865
I guarantee

59:39.325 --> 59:41.578
you'll go to a good place.

59:44.956 --> 59:45.999
Farewell.

01:01:35.942 --> 01:01:38.945
OKCHEON BUILDING

01:01:43.991 --> 01:01:45.910
- Is it all over?
- Yes.

01:01:45.993 --> 01:01:48.663
Your son is inside. Go on ahead.

01:01:49.372 --> 01:01:50.748
Father.

01:01:50.832 --> 01:01:51.833
Yes?

01:01:51.916 --> 01:01:53.960
Thank you so much.

01:01:54.794 --> 01:01:55.795
Don't mention it.

01:01:56.963 --> 01:01:57.964
Goodbye.

01:02:06.264 --> 01:02:09.267
JOB APPLICATION
NAME: SHIN I-RANG

01:02:14.105 --> 01:02:15.314
Are you busy?

01:02:17.483 --> 01:02:18.818
What brings you here, Mom?

01:02:20.403 --> 01:02:24.782
I'm here to feed my attorney son
who's working late hours.

01:02:29.620 --> 01:02:30.621
Mom,

01:02:31.205 --> 01:02:32.915
about Dad…

01:02:36.335 --> 01:02:37.336
What about him?

01:02:40.423 --> 01:02:42.133
Never mind.

01:02:43.593 --> 01:02:44.594
What is it?

01:02:48.347 --> 01:02:49.348
You know,

01:02:50.099 --> 01:02:52.226
when we arrived at the hospital,

01:02:53.644 --> 01:02:55.438
he was already dead.

01:02:57.857 --> 01:02:59.150
I'm wondering

01:03:00.067 --> 01:03:02.278
if he wanted to tell us anything.

01:03:04.447 --> 01:03:05.948
If he did,

01:03:07.700 --> 01:03:11.579
he might show up to us at least once.

01:03:15.541 --> 01:03:16.876
Nonsense.

01:03:22.423 --> 01:03:23.424
Well,

01:03:24.258 --> 01:03:26.344
I guess it wouldn't be so bad
if he did show up.

01:03:28.971 --> 01:03:31.974
I have tons of questions for him too.

01:03:38.272 --> 01:03:39.774
Eat up before it gets cold.

01:03:39.857 --> 01:03:41.108
Don't be home too late.

01:03:41.818 --> 01:03:42.819
See you.

01:03:43.361 --> 01:03:44.403
You're leaving already?

01:05:10.531 --> 01:05:11.532
That's right.

01:05:12.283 --> 01:05:14.827
Let's say the worst is behind us now

01:05:14.911 --> 01:05:16.329
and make a fresh start.

01:05:22.168 --> 01:05:23.419
This should be enough

01:05:23.502 --> 01:05:26.756
to ward off even the oldest ghosts.

01:05:28.591 --> 01:05:30.009
LEGAL CONSULTATION, LEGAL ADVICE
SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE

01:06:16.722 --> 01:06:19.016
How may I help you, girl?

01:06:24.063 --> 01:06:26.148
What brings you here?

01:06:31.529 --> 01:06:33.030
Mister,

01:06:34.031 --> 01:06:35.324
you can see me?

01:06:35.950 --> 01:06:36.951
What?

01:06:52.341 --> 01:06:53.342
Not again.

01:06:55.011 --> 01:06:57.763
Why does it keep happening to me?

01:07:36.510 --> 01:07:39.388
You looked so cool
when you were dancing earlier.

01:07:39.472 --> 01:07:42.141
<i>A trainee committed suicide</i>
<i>and the fans are going wild.</i>

01:07:42.224 --> 01:07:43.517
Let me look into it.

01:07:43.601 --> 01:07:44.769
<i>- Loanne was…</i>
- Hey!

01:07:44.852 --> 01:07:46.854
Stop causing harm to others
and just go home.

01:07:46.937 --> 01:07:49.523
<i>The girls found it hard to deal with her.</i>

01:07:49.607 --> 01:07:51.108
Her phone disappeared from the scene.

01:07:51.192 --> 01:07:52.526
<i>You think she was murdered?</i>

01:07:52.610 --> 01:07:54.111
<i>Let's go catch the culprit.</i>

01:07:54.195 --> 01:07:55.237
<i>Do you know who Loanne is?</i>

01:07:55.321 --> 01:07:56.822
<i>- Who are you?</i>
<i>- Who are you? A reporter?</i>

01:07:56.906 --> 01:07:58.699
<i>How did you get in? Let's go.</i>

01:07:58.783 --> 01:08:00.326
<i>I heard a phone ring.</i>

01:08:02.203 --> 01:08:03.996
<i>I never heard that ringtone before.</i>

01:08:04.080 --> 01:08:09.085
Subtitle translation by: Eunjin Erica Kim
